<h2 id="expressions">Expressions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Mrs. Hurst and Miss Bingley had spent some hours of the morning with <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="the invalid"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(病人)</code></b>, who continued, though slowly, to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="mend"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(身体好转)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Elizabeth took up some needlework, and was sufficiently amused in <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="attending to"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(倾听)</code></b> <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="what passed between Darcy and his companion"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(Darcy和他的同伴之间的对话)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Your humility must <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="disarm reproof"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(让人想责备你也不忍了[意译，直译 - 消除责备])</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Mrs. Bennet and her daughters then departed, and Elizabeth returned instantly to Jane, leaving her own and her relations’ behavior to the remarks of the two ladies and Mr. Darcy, the latter of whom, however, could not be <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="prevailed on to"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(劝说做某事)</code></b> join in their censure of her, in spite of all Miss Bingley’s witticism on fine eyes.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>How many letters you must <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="have occasion to"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(有必要做...需要做...)</code></b> write in the course of a year?</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>It is fortunate, then, that they <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="fall to my lot"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(落到我的肩上)</code></b> instead of to yours.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>She had high <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="animal spirits"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(生气/活力)</code></b>, and a sort of natural <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="self-consequence"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(自尊自大/SELF-IMPORTANCE)</code></b>, which the attentions of the officers, to whom her uncle’s good dinners and her own easy manners <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="recommended to | These qualities recommended him to Olivier. 这些品质让他备受Olivier的青睐。"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(使...对某人有优势/意译 - 使...对她青睐有加)</code></b>, had <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="increased into assurance"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(增添了自信)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The perpetual commendations of the lady either on his hand-writing, or on <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="the evenness of his lines"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(一行行字迹整齐)</code></b>, or on the length of his letter, with the perfect unconcern with which her praises were received, formed a curious dialogue, and was exactly <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="in unison with"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(符合)</code></b> her opinion of each.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>When you told Mrs. Bennet this morning that if you ever <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="resolved on (doing something)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(决心做某事)</code></b>quitting Netherfield you should be gone in five minutes, you meant it to be a sort of panegyric, of compliment to yourself – and yet <strong>what is there so very laudable in a precipitance</strong> which must leave very necessary business undone, and can be of no real advantage to yourself or anyone else?</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Allowing the case, to stand according to your representation"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(不过就算情况像你说的那样)</code></b>, you must remember, Miss Bennet, that the friend who is supposed to desire his return to the house and the delay of his plan, has merely desired it, asked it <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="without offering one argument in favor of its propriety"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(未给出理由说明其要求是合理的)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="It is a rule with me"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(我始终认为)</code></b>, that a person who can write a long letter with ease cannot <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="write ill"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(写作不会差)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>You have only proved by this, that Mr. Bingley did not <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="do justice to his own disposition || do justice - to treat someone or something in a way that is fair and shows their or its true qualities"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(由着自己的性子为所欲为)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But I am afraid you are <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="giving it a turn"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(你的这种圆转)</code></b> which that gentleman did by no means intend, for he would certainly <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="think the better of me"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(更看得起我)</code></b>, if under such a circumstance I were to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="give a flat denial"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(爽快地拒绝)</code></b>, and ride off as fast as I could.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
